<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-709-704  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 709 704.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>MIS Week  Sept 4 1989 v10 n35 p12(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Tuning tools sharpen applications. (software programs thatfine-tune applications)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Leinfuss, Emily.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Applications tuning products enable an analyst to monitor andpinpoint areas of inefficient code in an application and allow amainframe to run more efficiently.andP;  Companies who optimize theircomputing environment can prolong the life of their hardware,postpone CPU upgrades, and save money in computer time.andP;  Someproducts are TSA/PPE, Dexan, CA-Optimizer, and Strobe.andP;  TSA/PPE,from Boole and Babbage Inc and Candle Corp's Dexan are bothsystems tuning products.andP;  CA-Optimizer, from Computer AssociatesInternational, only tunes DB2 products.andP;  Programart's Strobe hasoptional features for tuning applications in IMS, CICS/VS, IDMSand DVS, but is limited to MVS environments and applications only.andO;A Strobe user who tuned just one application expects to save asmuch as $150,000 a year.Computer-aided software engineering (CASE)tools can be used in conjunction to help re-engineer applications.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Boole and Babbage Inc. (products)Candle Corp. (products)Computer Associates International Inc. (products)Computer Systems Architects Inc. Programart (products).andO;Product:   TSA/PPE (Computer program) (usage)Dexan (Computer program) (usage)CA-Optimizer (Computer program) (usage)Strobe (Computer program) (usage).andO;Topic:     ApplicationsSoftware PackagesTuningMaintenanceComputer-Aided Software EngineeringMainframe Computers.andO;Feature:   illustrationcartoon.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>